request.doc:
POST https://{appliance_hostname}/mga/runtime_tuning/endpoints/v1
Creating an endpoint with a static IP address: Note that the format of interface is <interface UUID>.<address UUID>
POST_DATA: {"interface": "38a69185-a61a-44a1-b574-a3b502f01414.f980aabe-80b7-4738-9cda-bccede8d34f2", "port": 80, "secure": false}
Creating an endpoint with a DHCP IP address: Note that the format of interface is <interface UUID>.dhcp.<ip version>, where <ip version> is given as "ipv4" or "ipv6".
POST_DATA: {"interface": "fb61cf92-a126-4d9d-9ef9-8dc3cf8ba298.dhcp.ipv4", "port": 443, "secure": true}
Creating an endpoint which listens on all available application (non-management) addresses:
POST_DATA: {"interface": "all-application-interfaces", "port": 444, "secure": true}
To discover the interface and IP address UUIDs, refer to the following topic: Manage: System Settings > Network Settings > Interfaces

response.doc:
200 OK
Content-Type:application/json

A created endpoint with a static IP address:
{"id": "38a69185-a61a-44a1-b574-a3b502f01414.f980aabe-80b7-4738-9cda-bccede8d34f2:80"}

A created endpoint with a DHCP IP address:
{"id": "fb61cf92-a126-4d9d-9ef9-8dc3cf8ba298.dhcp.ipv4:443"}

A created endpoint which listens on all available application (non-management) addresses:
{"id": "all-application-interfaces:444"}

Note that the "id" values are in the format <given interface value>:<given port value>
This is the value which should be used as the identifier in the URL for future update/delete requests.
